The paper discusses a system for secure execution of Linux binaries inside Intel SGX enclaves, which involves protecting the interface between the enclave and the untrusted host OS. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cryptography (cs.CR), operating systems (cs.OS), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, given the focus on security and protection of data, cs.CR and cs.OS are the most likely sub-categories.
